<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Odd program quirks (that I'd like to make default operat]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6967&amp;p=29827#p29827"><![CDATA[
Yes, Classic Shell can replace the All Programs menu in the Windows 7 start menu and make it cascading. It is controlled by the setting &quot;Cascading All Programs menu&quot; in the &quot;Windows Start Menu&quot; tab.<br /><br />The &quot;Right click opens the Windows context menu&quot; setting in the &quot;Controls&quot; tab determines what happens if you right-click on the start button.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Fri Oct 14, 2016 4:28 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
