<title type="html"><![CDATA[Odd program quirks (that I'd like to make default operation!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6967&amp;p=29824#p29824"><![CDATA[
My system and software:<br />Windows 7 64-bit<br />NVidia GTX 980<br />Classic Shell version: 4.3.0<br />Windowblinds version: 10<br /><br />So yes, I'm using Classic Shell and Windowblinds together.  I love them both!!<br />But I have an odd quirk with the start menu.<br /><br />I generally use CSM with Classic Style start menu.  I love the cascading menus from the old WinXP days...<br />However, what I would *really* like, is to be able to use the real Windows Start Menu, but force it into cascading-menus format.<br />Of course, if I use CSM, I get the cascading menus that I want, but it's with the CSM skin (somewhat modified by Windowblinds).<br /><br />I've been cruising along with this, and been pretty happy; I *still* love CSM, but the rest of my windows are *soooo* beautiful!!  I wish I could use them on Start Menu, yet still get the cascading menus... not the end of the world, but it would be nice...<br /><br /><em><span style="text-decoration: underline">Okay, I told you that so I could tell you this...</span></em><br />Every once in awhile, an odd thing happens - somehow, I'll get the desktop into a mode where when I right-click on the Start Menu, I'll get the original start menu (*not* the CSM), but when I click on Programs, I get cascading menus !!!!  Exactly what I want - except that I don't know what makes that happen... ???  After a couple of menu clicks, Start Menu goes back to normal CSM operation, and right-click on the Start button displays the Classic Shell config menu.<br /><br />Well, I've noticed an odd thing at the moment.  Right now, if I click on the desktop, then press SPACE, then right-click on the Start button, I get exactly what I want - the traditional Start Menu, but with cascading Program menus.<br />Later note: no, that's stopped happening, right-click on the Start button is giving the Classic Shell config menu again.<br /><br />So what is going on??  Is there some way I can make right-click *always* give me the traditional Start Menu, but with cascading Program menus??  This is *very* confusing...<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=330">Gorlash</a> — Fri Oct 14, 2016 3:48 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
